,Not Recommended,443580,30181474,Posted: 25 February,all,Sadie,"Interesting concept, disappointing execution. I love this kind of short, introspective game, but this one pales in comparison to some of the others out there. The radio mechanic is cool, but we're able to use it just twice, and the rest of the experience doesn't engage the player. There was atmosphere, but it was minimal (in feeling, not just design), and the fact that every action the player takes must be directed with on-screen cues reflect the fact that without them, this game wouldn't make sense - it's just not intuitive.If you'd like an atmospheric, visually and mechanically interesting game, play The Old Tree. It's meditative, reflective, and beautiful."
