76561198090501756,Recommended,443580,30198127,Posted: 26 February,all,redsnowyo,"(If the 'w' key does nothing when you start, reset your game and try it again.)This game is super pretty and speaks volumes of its environment with so few details. The puzzles give you just enough direction to let you figure out on your own what you need to do, which is something I've felt is lacking in a lot of puzzles lately. It walks a fine line between too little instruction and just enough, which I honestly adore.The puzzles require patience and force you to find solutions one baby step at a time; it DOES feel like you're just a little robot exploring and trying its hardest.Maybe a ten minute playthrough once you know what you're doing? Fun. I'd love to see more levels and/or more games like this from the designer(s)."
